MANAGEMENT TEAM
Our experienced management team prides itself on years of real-world experience and numerous accreditations. 
            We design wealth management and investment management solutions delivered with the highest level of personalized service. About Professional Designations
........................................................................
          
          CURT SNYDER, CPA, CFA - Managing Partner
Experience:
            Curt Snyder is a founding partner of Towercrest Capital and brings over 23 years of industry experience to the firm. Mr. Snyder provides investment advice while constructing and managing portfolios for individuals and institutions. A Chartered Financial Analyst (CFA) and a Certified Public Accountant (CPA), Mr. Snyder is one of the few investment advisors who have earned both of these professional designations. Before forming Towercrest Capital, Mr. Snyder was a partner and CFO of Brigade Capital Management, a NYC asset management firm. Prior to Brigade Capital Management, Mr. Snyder served as CFO, America Investments, for Merrill Lynch Investment Managers. The investment groups that Mr. Snyder served as CFO managed assets in excess of $350 billion, of which $15 billion were in Alternative Investments, $200 billion in Fixed Income, and $135 billion in Equities. Prior to that, he held senior financial management positions at JP Morgan Chase, Wasserstein Perella, and Ernst & Young.
          Education/Credentials:
            Drexel University - MBA in Finance 
            Bloomsburg University - B.S. in Accounting 
            CFA Charterholder 
            Member of the CFA Institute & New York Society of Security Analysts 
            Certified Public Accountant 
          ........................................................................
GRIFFIN HAVIKEN, CPA - Managing Partner
Experience:
  Griffin Haviken is a founding partner of Towercrest Capital and brings over 20 years of industry experience to the firm. Mr. Haviken provides investment advice while constructing and managing portfolios for individuals and institutions. Before forming Towercrest Capital, Mr. Haviken was a Director at Merrill Lynch. Over the course of his eleven year career at Merrill, Mr. Haviken held senior financial management positions in the Global Wealth Management (GWM) division and the Global Markets & Investment Banking (GMI) division. Previous to Merrill Lynch, Mr. Haviken worked as an analyst at Morgan Stanley and Barclays Capital. Mr. Haviken began his career in the Financial Services & Hedge Fund Division of the NYC public accounting firm Goldstein, Golub, Kessler (“GGK”). Mr. Haviken is a Certified Public Accountant and has also passed the Series 65 Uniform Investment Advisor Law Examination. 
Education/Credentials:
            Fordham University - MBA in Finance
            SUNY Albany - B.S. in Accounting
            Certified Public Accountant
            Series 65
 




