 of 2017-03-31.Added: American International Group Inc (AIG)Towercrest Capital Management added to the holdings in American International Group Inc by 43.43%. The purchase prices were between $60.85 and $67.2, with an estimated average price of $64.21. The stock is now traded at around $61.99. The impact to the portfolio due to this purchase was 1.45%. The holdings were 89,440 shares as of 2017-03-31.Added: iShares Core MSCI Emerging Markets (IEMG)Towercrest Capital Management added to the holdings in iShares Core MSCI Emerging Markets by 38.67%. The purchase prices were between $42.45 and $48.5, with an estimated average price of $46.01. The stock is now traded at around $49.82. The impact to the portfolio due to this purchase was 1.3%. The holdings were 114,004 shares as of 2017-03-31.Added: SPDR Bloomberg Barclays High Yield Bond (JNK)Towercrest Capital Management added to the holdings in SPDR Bloomberg Barclays High Yield Bond by 21.07%. The purchase prices were between $36.25 and $37.22, with an estimated average price of $36.79. The stock is now traded at around $37.30. The impact to the portfolio due to this purchase was 0.29%. The holdings were 52,490 shares as of 2017-03-31.Sold Out: SPDR Nuveen Bloomberg Barclays Municipal Bond (TFI)Towercrest Capital Management sold out the holdings in SPDR Nuveen Bloomberg Barclays Municipal Bond. The sale prices were between $47.26 and $48.08, with an estimated average price of $47.65.Reduced: iShares 1-3 Year Treasury Bond (SHY)Towercrest Capital Management reduced to the holdings in iShares 1-3 Year Treasury Bond by 73.96%. The sale prices were between $84.24 and $84.63, with an estimated average price of $84.46. The stock is now traded at around $84.56. The impact to the portfolio due to this sale was -1.41%. Towercrest Capital Management still held 6,573 shares as of 2017-03-31.Reduced: JPMorgan Chase & Co (JPM)Towercrest Capital Management reduced to the holdings in JPMorgan Chase & Co by 22.49%. The sale prices were between $83.3 and $93.6, with an estimated average price of $88.22. The stock is now traded at around $85.49. The impact to the portfolio due to this sale was -0.08%. Towercrest Capital Management still held 3,447 shares as of 2017-03-31.MUB 15-Year Financial DataThe intrinsic value of MUBPeter Lynch Chart of MUBPremium MembersThis article first appeared on GuruFocus .



